{
  "stem": "8892.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Then all of a sudden, one day my father gets a letter that he does not own his home, which he inherited from his father-- my grandfather-- the butcher shop, and they stripped him from legally owning a business.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So he actually had to pay, to the town, rent on his own property.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But because there was no other butcher-- just one and only in the small town, who slaughtered only pork, which my father never had, they had to have somebody running the show.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So they gave him back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He was promoted, then, because he was in the First World War, and-- and he was a Russian prisoner, and God knows the stories they used to say.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And because of all of this, he finally got back his business.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he got back the permit that he must be a butcher, and he must supply the town with their meat.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And, of course, they started to ration it even for the Gentiles and, of course, no kosher meat for a Jew.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That was the first thing they took away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my recollection out of all this, this is when I started to live in fear and-- and be scared, because my father would go.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He wouldn't just lie down and do nothing, so he would conduct like a [INAUDIBLE] He would bring-- he couldn't do the [NON-ENGLISH], you know, the guy that-- what they call that?",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The [NON-ENGLISH], I think, who slaughters the cow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father never did it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And how do you spell [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[HEBREW] is a Jewish word, and I don't know what the-- even in-- well, in Hungarian, they call it [HUNGARIAN].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The one who studies-- just like a mohel-- who studies just to slaughter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What they call it?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Oh, a [HEBREW], I think.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
